
Extensions are plugins that enhance Burp Suite's functionality. These plugins enable customization of security testing processes, adding new features, and automating various tasks.
Installed extensions usually appear as a new tab, menu item, or toolbar button in the Burp Suite user interface. To use an extension, click on the new interface element and follow the extension's instructions.

• Installing from the BApp Store
• Manual Installation
• Popular Burp Suite Extensions
• Updating and Removing Extensions
• APIs


-- Installing from the BApp Store --

1. Access Extension Tab: Go to the "Extensions" tab in Burp Suite.
2. Select BApp Store: Click on the "BApp Store" tab to view the list of available extensions.
3. Install Extension: Find the extension you are interested in and click the "Install" button to install it.


-- Manual Installation --

1. Download Extension File: Prepare the extension file (.jar or .py) that you will download.
2. Go to Extensions Tab: Open the "Extensions" tab.
3. Click "Add" Button: Click on the "Add" button.
4. Enter Extension Details: Select the type of extension (Java or Python) and locate the file using "Select file."
5. Install: Click "Next" or "OK" to install the extension.


-- Popular Burp Suite Extensions --

• Turbo Intruder: A powerful HTTP attack tool that allows sending HTTP requests quickly for advanced attacks.
• SQLMap for Burp Suite: An extension that allows the use of popular SQLMap's features within Burp Suite to automatically detect and exploit SQL injection vulnerabilities.
• Autorize: Helps in automatically checking authorization controls, used to discover access control vulnerabilities.
• Active Scan++: Enhances Burp Suite's built-in passive and active scanning capabilities to detect a wider range of security vulnerabilities.
• 403 Bypasser: Used to automatically test methods to bypass access restrictions (HTTP 403 Forbidden) in web applications.


-- Updating and Removing Extensions --

• Extensions are usually updated automatically or manually. For extensions installed from the BApp Store, check for updates in the "Extensions" tab and follow the instructions.
• To remove an extension, select it from the "Extensions" list and click the "Remove" button.


-- APIs --

Burp Suite provides APIs that allow developers to extend and customize various functions of Burp Suite. 
Through APIs, developers can create their own extensions, automate existing workflows, and develop new features that integrate into Burp Suite's security testing processes.



